# $Id$
#
# Radius Group membership checking
#

Module depends on: -

This module export functions necesarry for group membership
checking over radius. There is a database table that contains list of 
users and groups they belong to. The table is used by functions of 
this module.

Exported Parameters:
-------------------

Name:    radius_config
Type:    str
Default: "/usr/local/etc/radiusclient/radiusclient.conf"
Desc:    Location of the configuration file of the radius client
         library

Name:    use_domain
Type:    int
Default: 0 (no)
Desc:    If set to 1 then username@domain will be
         used for lookup, if set to 0 then only
	 username will be used


Exported Functions:
------------------

Name:   radius_is_user_in
Params: URI - URI whose username and optionally domain to be
              used, this can be one of:
	      Request-URI -- use Request-URI username and domain
	      To -- Use To username and domain
	      From -- Use From username and domain
	      Credentials -- Use digest credentials username
	group - Name of the group to check
Desc:   The function returns true if username in the given URI is
        member of the given group and false if not.
